 Gain Persistence with schtasks, Registry Run Keys, and WMImplant
Objectives
By the end of this lab, students will be able to:

Understand Windows persistence mechanisms used by adversaries
Simulate scheduled task persistence using Python-based tools
Implement registry run key persistence techniques
Deploy WMI-based persistence mechanisms
Analyze and detect persistence from a defensive perspective
Prerequisites
Basic understanding of Windows operating system concepts
Familiarity with command-line interfaces and Python programming
Understanding of Windows registry and scheduled tasks
Lab Environment
This lab uses a Linux-based cloud machine that simulates Windows persistence techniques through Python scripts. All tools are pre-installed. Click Start Lab to begin.

